# API / Shopify

## Structure

- Register routes in `src/app.ts`. Keep domain logic in `src/lib/**`, not inline in route handlers.
- Existing domains: `lib/billing`, `lib/analytics`, `lib/escalation`, `lib/shopify`, `lib/ai-runner`.
- Auth via `plugins/auth` + `resolveMerchant` / `resolveAgent`. Return `{ error: { message, statusCode } }` consistently.

## Shopify

- Admin GraphQL only through `lib/shopify/graphql.ts` (`shopifyFetch`).
- Webhooks: verify HMAC, idempotent via `WebhookDelivery`, return **401** only for bad signatures.
- Topic path mapping: `topicToPath` / `pathToTopic` — topics with underscores (e.g. `app_subscriptions/update`) need an explicit `pathToTopic` special case.
- Access tokens: encrypt on write, decrypt only when calling Shopify.

## Billing & usage

- Plans: `lib/billing/plans.ts`. Subscriptions: `lib/billing/shopify-billing.ts`. Quotas: `lib/billing/usage.ts`.
- Count usage **only** for AI-resolved conversations (`recordAiResolutionUsage`), never human-handled.
- Gate AI with `enforceAiUsage` before `runConversationAi`. Hard limit returns the human-only message.
- Paid plan changes use Shopify confirmation URLs; do not set `planTier` to paid until `verifySubscription` succeeds.

## Data

- Prisma schema changes require a migration SQL file. Prefer additive, idempotent `IF NOT EXISTS` when safe.
- Fire-and-forget analytics via `trackEvent` (batched); do not block request paths on ClickHouse.
